Sentencas: In this work, the effects of the La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) electrode-yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte interface on the stability of LSCF electrodes under high-current electrolysis are studied.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Six different half cells with different configurations are tested at 800 degrees C for 264 h under an electrolysis current of 1 A cm(-2).
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: A few concluding remarks can be drawn by comparing the behaviors of different cells.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Firstly, it is confirmed that the formation of SrZrO3 at the interface will lead to the delamination of air electrode.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Thus, the formation of SrZrO3 should be strictly prevented.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Secondly, increasing sintering temperature can decrease the degradation rate of polarization resistance, R-p, for LSCF electrodes.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Thirdly, the increase of ohmic resistance, R-s, comes from structural changes as the degradation rate in percentage is similar for cells with different electrolytes and electrodes.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Fourthly, the LSCF electrode after the electrolysis test shows recrystallization and lattice shrink which could be the reason for the degradation of LSCF electrodes on Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) electrolytes.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells

Sentencas: Lastly, comparing all the samples, the cell composed of YSZ electrolyte, dense GDC interlayer and LSCF electrode sintered at 1000 degrees C can be used for future study on the degradation mechanisms of the LSCF air electrode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ air electrode electrolyte interface on the short-term stability under high-current electrolysis in solid oxide electrolyzer cells
